342
00:34:54,615 --> 00:34:56,359
Because I wanna smoke.

343
00:34:57,118 --> 00:34:58,825
Come over here.

344
00:35:00,663 --> 00:35:03,118
Now, do your shoe-laces on.

345
00:35:07,836 --> 00:35:10,621
What time is our flight
to Florida, Seymore?

346
00:35:12,338 --> 00:35:14,461
I think two o'clock, Derek.

347
00:35:19,303 --> 00:35:21,046
Let's go, Seymore.

348
00:35:45,991 --> 00:35:48,233
Holy shit!

349
00:36:31,778 --> 00:36:33,854
- Are you ready?
- Ready for what?

350
00:36:33,946 --> 00:36:36,615
- You wanted to see what I do, right?
- Yes!

351
00:36:37,491 --> 00:36:39,235
Yes, I've been watching...

352
00:36:40,410 --> 00:36:44,158
Showtime is over,
the real deal is about to start.

353
00:36:44,705 --> 00:36:46,248
"The real deal"?

354
00:36:48,667 --> 00:36:50,873
Showtime is for sissies.

355
00:36:51,378 --> 00:36:52,919
But a sissy I'm not.

356
00:36:55,339 --> 00:36:57,082
- Come on!
- We got fire!

357
00:36:57,633 --> 00:36:58,912
- That's for the distraction.
- Easy.

358
00:36:58,967 --> 00:37:02,252
Fire will distract most cops.

359
00:37:02,929 --> 00:37:04,470
Are you ready to finish what we started?

360
00:37:04,512 --> 00:37:07,633
Julian, that was extremely dangerous...
I think you proved your point.

361
00:37:09,517 --> 00:37:13,017
The cops may have gone to the fire,
but his bodyguard is probably still upfront.

362
00:37:13,062 --> 00:37:14,176
Bodyguard?

363
00:37:14,313 --> 00:37:16,638
Those who are afraid of being killed,
always have a bodyguard.

364
00:37:16,690 --> 00:37:18,932
If they didn't... They'd asked you.

365
00:37:18,983 --> 00:37:21,556
So, I'd slit the guards throat,
push him back at the bathroom...

366
00:37:24,405 --> 00:37:26,563
And now we're set up for the kill.

367
00:37:30,868 --> 00:37:32,528
Were the hell did you get the knife?

368
00:37:32,619 --> 00:37:34,991
It must be number two...

369
00:37:35,038 --> 00:37:38,371
- Okey, joke's over... let's go, Julian!
-Not yet!

370
00:37:38,666 --> 00:37:40,658
