...is that I don't have a home.
I mean...

733
01:06:59,094 --> 01:07:00,967
That's why I'm here.

734
01:07:02,931 --> 01:07:05,137
You're the only friends I have.

735
01:07:06,058 --> 01:07:10,186
But that's ridiculous...
you have friends.

736
01:07:13,356 --> 01:07:16,356
I don't, I really don't.

737
01:07:17,943 --> 01:07:22,355
You're it,
it's fucking crazy, right?

738
01:07:23,573 --> 01:07:25,695
You're my only friends
and I barely know you.

739
01:07:28,285 --> 01:07:29,827
This home...

740
01:07:32,539 --> 01:07:34,365
Your home...

741
01:07:36,500 --> 01:07:38,576
...is the only home I know.

742
01:07:42,463 --> 01:07:44,751
She's really fantastic, Danny.

743
01:07:45,591 --> 01:07:48,876
- She's lovely.
- She means everything to me.

744
01:07:49,427 --> 01:07:51,668
You said that to me in Mexico.

745
01:07:52,471 --> 01:07:57,262
I nodded and listened,
but now I see.

746
01:07:58,601 --> 01:08:00,511
I see...

747
01:08:07,775 --> 01:08:11,144
Did you told her everything that
happened in Mexico?

748
01:08:13,321 --> 01:08:16,737
I told her about our time together, yes.

749
01:08:18,743 --> 01:08:21,067
And where does that story end?

750
01:08:24,873 --> 01:08:26,664
She knows the last I heard of you-

751
01:08:26,749 --> 01:08:29,074
- you where knocking on my hotel-room
in the middle of the night-

752
01:08:29,126 --> 01:08:32,043
- asking forgiveness for trying
to involve me in a job.

753
01:08:34,798 --> 01:08:39,505
That's what you said?
That I knocked and knocked...

754
01:08:40,302 --> 01:08:44,880
- And you never answered?
- Yes.

755
01:08:46,973 --> 01:08:48,551
Gentlemen!

756
01:08:50,726 --> 01:08:52,720
I'm a bit drunk.

757
01:08:53,645 --> 01:08:55,354
It's a nice place to be.

758
01:08:55,522 --> 01:08:58,772
Julian, you will stay the night of course?

759
01:08:59,693 --> 01:09:02,812
Thank you, Bean. I promise
I'll be out of here tomorrow.

760
01:09:02,945 --> 01:09:05,317
Let's not talk about that now.

761
01:09:05,656 --> 01:09:10,401
I don't think I've been up with guests
til 2:30 in the morning... in a long time.

762
01:09:10,452 --> 01:09:13,452
- It's good, right?
- Oh, it's very good.

763
01:09:14,413 --> 01:09:17,781
- Can I turn on your stereo?
- Sure... now?

764
01:09:18,166 --> 01:09:22,707
Yeah, I saw an old record of yours that I'd
like to hear in the small hours the morning.

765
01:09:22,961 --> 01:09:27,208
Since we're in the small hours
of the morning, is that okey?

766
01:09:27,548 --> 01:09:30,004
Certainly.
Yes, yes...

767
01:09:44,645 --> 01:09:46,140
Danny?

768
01:09:46,606 --> 01:09:52,274
I hope you approve, I'd really want
to ask your wife for a dance.

769
01:09:55,779 --> 01:09:58,234
Julian, you've had to much to drink.

770
01:10:00,575 --> 01:10:04,323
Bean... please, may I have this dance?

771
01:11:05,003 --> 01:11:09,249
Bravo...! Bravo!

772
01:11:10,549 --> 01:11:14,463
I learnt to dance in a
south-american jail.

773
01:11:14,594 --> 01:11:17,215
Well, that's another story...
another time.

774
01:11:17,429 --> 01:11:18,709
The final night-cap!

775
01:11:18,763 --> 01:11:21,432
I can't even think of
how I'll get up in the morning.

776
01:11:21,474 --> 01:11:23,016
Then don't!
What you do...

777
01:11:23,059 --> 01:11:26,012
take 3 aspirins in a row,
before you go to bed tonight.

778
01:11:26,061 --> 01:11:29,512
Where'd you hear that one?
Assassins book of home-remedys?

779
01:11:34,527 --> 01:11:36,851
The only woman that I ever loved...

780
01:11:37,029 --> 01:11:38,653
...my mother.

781
01:11:39,322 --> 01:11:41,279
What about your wife?

782
01:11:42,450 --> 01:11:43,612
My wife?

783
01:11:43,701 --> 01:11:47,199
Danny told me that you were married,
and that she died in a car-accident.

784
01:11:47,245 --> 01:11:48,703
You loved her!

785
01:12:01,423 --> 01:12:03,001
Oh, my God!

786
01:12:03,300 --> 01:12:06,087
- I can't believe this!
- I was never married.

787
01:12:06,511 --> 01:12:07,886
I can't believe this...

788
01:12:07,970 --> 01:12:10,425
- There wasn't a car-accident?
- No.

789
01:12:10,472 --> 01:12:13,888
I'd been insensitive to Danny, about your
son, and I was trying to win him over-

790
01:12:13,933 --> 01:12:17,467
- it was juvenile, stupid. - You know what,
Julian, I'm the one that was stupid!

791
01:12:17,686 --> 01:12:20,557
No, no, no, you're not stupid.
I'm a prick!

792
01:12:20,605 --> 01:12:22,230
It's me, not you!

793
01:12:22,690 --> 01:12:25,976
I could have kept lying now,
but I chose not to, as a sign of..

794
01:12:26,236 --> 01:12:29,900
-respect... because now, we're friends.

795
01:12:32,074 --> 01:12:33,781
We are friends, aren't we?

796
01:12:34,659 --> 01:12:37,030
What other bullshit
did you pour over me, Julian?

797
01:12:37,077 --> 01:12:38,821
Are you even a hitman, Julian?

798
01:12:41,664 --> 01:12:43,039
-or what the fuck you call yourself.

799
01:12:43,541 --> 01:12:46,114
Yes, I am.
Is that the answer to your question, Danny?

800
01:12:46,669 --> 01:12:49,622
I lie when I need to.
And tell the truth when I can.

801
01:12:49,670 --> 01:12:51,414
With you...

802
01:12:52,924 --> 01:12:55,212
It's mostly been the truth.

803
01:13:04,183 --> 01:13:05,725
Should I go?

804
01:13:11,272 --> 01:13:13,263
- No.
- No.

805
01:13:20,863 --> 01:13:23,235
Aren't we fucking cosmopolitan?

806
01:13:24,198 --> 01:13:27,366
Having a trained assassin,
stay over the night?

807
01:13:27,743 --> 01:13:32,321
Letting heartbreaking lies
roll over us, like the summer-breeze.

808
01:13:32,747 --> 01:13:35,072
Next we should be wife-swapping?

809
01:13:37,543 --> 01:13:40,543
You don't have a wife...
remember?

810
01:13:48,176 --> 01:13:50,300
That's a good point.

811
01:14:05,775 --> 01:14:09,817
Danny... Danny!

812
01:14:16,115 --> 01:14:18,867
- Danny!
- No.. I have...

813
01:14:19,536 --> 01:14:21,908
Come on, I got to talk to you.

814
01:14:25,582 --> 01:14:27,290
What's it, Julian?
What do you want?

815
01:14:27,375 --> 01:14:30,411
- I can't talk about it here.
- What?

816
01:14:30,502 --> 01:14:31,831
Come on!

817
01:14:35,590 --> 01:14:39,290
Okey, Julian, we're in your rental-car.
What is it?

818
01:14:39,343 --> 01:14:43,175
The thing is, Danny...
the thing I didn't tell you.

819
01:14:43,931 --> 01:14:46,765
The thing I hide,
because Bean was present.

820
01:14:47,600 --> 01:14:51,644
Was that I've been offered a way out
of my fatal situation.

821
01:14:52,688 --> 01:14:54,229
- That's good.
- Yeah, I know.

822
01:14:54,272 --> 01:14:56,809
That's really good, what is it?

823
01:14:57,483 --> 01:15:00,851
My handler, mr Randy, contacted me
like he always does.

824
01:15:00,902 --> 01:15:04,235
With an add in the international tribune
looking cat-salers in Bali.

825
01:15:04,363 --> 01:15:08,112
Is that how you stayed in contact?
Cats or the rats?

826
01:15:08,127 --> 01:15:09,368
Yeah.

827
01:15:09,700 --> 01:15:12,987
Okey, this is ridiculous,
I'm so tired, Julian.

828
01:15:14,163 --> 01:15:17,946
He contacted me 4 days ago, and basically,
he said he's been at the higher-ups.

829
01:15:18,958 --> 01:15:20,702
And got me a reprieve.

830
01:15:20,835 --> 01:15:23,705
Well like I said,
that's great news!

831
01:15:23,754 --> 01:15:28,130
The thing is, he's asking me
to do one more job.

832
01:15:28,467 --> 01:15:31,038
I have no choice,
it's do the job, or else...

833
01:15:32,219 --> 01:15:35,172
And it brings us to the
dirty little problem.

834
01:15:39,934 --> 01:15:41,214
What's the problem?

835
01:15:41,269 --> 01:15:43,261
Well, actually it's a pretty big problem.

836
01:15:43,478 --> 01:15:44,937
And you really not gonna like it.

837
01:15:45,438 --> 01:15:47,348
- I'm not gonna like it?
- Not at all.

838
01:15:48,273 --> 01:15:52,687
Because the job... involves you.

839
01:15:57,114 --> 01:15:59,190
You're not saying,
what I think you're saying?

840
01:16:00,158 --> 01:16:02,281
What do you think I'm saying?

841
01:16:02,828 --> 01:16:05,034
You know what I think you're saying...

842
01:16:05,371 --> 01:16:08,621
No, I don't think I know what you think,
I'm saying.

843
01:16:10,584 --> 01:16:12,660
Someone wants me dead?

844
01:16:24,554 --> 01:16:26,842
No, no one wants you dead, Danny!

845
01:16:35,687 --> 01:16:38,357
But I need your help
in facilitating the fatality.

846
01:16:38,398 --> 01:16:40,023
- What?
- I need your help.

847
01:16:40,067 --> 01:16:42,438
No, no, my help is exacly
what you don't need.

848
01:16:42,485 --> 01:16:44,607
I'm a mess, Danny.
You know that.

849
01:16:44,653 --> 01:16:47,938
I'm a complete mess,
I don't know if I can do this job by myself.

850
01:16:47,989 --> 01:16:50,776
You got to talk to somebody else,
a college!

851
01:16:50,825 --> 01:16:52,652
- I don't know any colleges.
- You must!

852
01:16:52,702 --> 01:16:55,192
- I don't.
- Well, I can't help you!

853
01:16:55,496 --> 01:16:57,738
Danny, I know you're not
the ideal-candidate.

854
01:16:57,789 --> 01:17:02,534
Ideal? Far, far from ideal, Julian.
Don't you remember my reaction-

855
01:17:02,585 --> 01:17:05,040
-the last time you proposed something
this utterly stupid?

856
01:17:05,086 --> 01:17:07,659
It was just in Mexico,
I was just trying to show you a good time!

857
01:17:07,713 --> 01:17:10,252
So now, killing somebody is a good time?

858
01:17:10,633 --> 01:17:12,256
It can be.

859
01:17:12,718 --> 01:17:14,840
- I'm going to sleep.
- Danny! Come on...

860
01:17:14,885 --> 01:17:16,510
Why do you need a second person?

861
01:17:16,554 --> 01:17:19,009
Haven't you done all these things yourself?

862
01:17:19,056 --> 01:17:21,013
Some jobs are better with two men.

863
01:17:21,058 --> 01:17:24,141
Well, I think it's better that the
2nd man isn't scared shitless...

864
01:17:24,185 --> 01:17:27,969
...and unprepared, and unqualified,
I'm not interested-

865
01:17:28,022 --> 01:17:29,646
-I'm gonna go to bed, Julian.

866
01:17:29,690 --> 01:17:32,061
I'm in a very dangerous
position here, Danny.

867
01:17:32,108 --> 01:17:34,350
I'm in no shape to try this myself.

868
01:17:34,402 --> 01:17:37,487
An assassin without confidence
is a horrible thing to behold.

869
01:17:37,821 --> 01:17:40,109
It's like a relief-picture
who fumbles the ball.

870
01:17:41,991 --> 01:17:44,363
Please, tell me you know you mixed
2 sports in your metaphor.

871
01:17:45,452 --> 01:17:46,697
I can't do that.

872
01:17:49,414 --> 01:17:52,285
Danny, please, please!
I need your help!

873
01:17:52,542 --> 01:17:54,914
Someone's gonna die.
A stranger, or me.

874
01:17:55,127 --> 01:17:56,704
Which would you rather?

875
01:17:58,170 --> 01:18:02,168
Look, if I can do the job successfully,
I'm free and clear.

876
01:18:02,216 --> 01:18:03,758
Free and clear, Danny!

877
01:18:03,801 --> 01:18:06,671
I have enough money saved up
to retire to a beautiful greek island-

878
01:18:06,720 --> 01:18:08,344
-with beautiful little greeks.

879
01:18:08,388 --> 01:18:10,795
Heaven awaits me, Danny,
if you and I do this job.

880
01:18:10,890 --> 01:18:13,345
- I can't!
- God damnit, Danny!

881
01:18:13,892 --> 01:18:15,931
- You're my only friend!
- Julian...!

882
01:18:15,976 --> 01:18:17,720
It's true, and...

883
01:18:20,147 --> 01:18:21,725
- What?
- And...

884
01:18:25,151 --> 01:18:26,859
You owe me...

885
01:18:31,198 --> 01:18:34,531
- If this would happen,
when would it take place? - Today.

886
01:18:34,951 --> 01:18:36,694
The horse-races.

887
01:18:37,579 --> 01:18:39,570
- Today?
- Yeah, in Arizona.

888
01:18:39,956 --> 01:18:41,947
No, no, that couldn't happen, Julian.

889
01:18:42,249 --> 01:18:43,624
No choice.

890
01:18:43,708 --> 01:18:47,408
No, today is the 4 year anniversary
of my son Henry's death.

891
01:18:47,877 --> 01:18:49,669
We go to the semetary.

892
01:18:49,754 --> 01:18:51,830
What time does the semetary close, Danny?

893
01:18:52,883 --> 01:18:54,340
I don't know...

894
01:18:54,466 --> 01:18:57,005
We'll have you back here 4:30,
I promise you.

895
01:18:57,052 --> 01:18:59,341
Oh, you do that, okey...

896
01:18:59,471 --> 01:19:01,380
Well, how will you do that, Julian?

897
01:19:01,973 --> 01:19:04,808
We have a 7:40 plane-reservation
to Tucson this morning.

898
01:19:05,184 --> 01:19:06,926
Plenty of time to catch the 2:30 back.

899
01:19:06,977 --> 01:19:08,435
We do?

900
01:19:08,520 --> 01:19:10,975
I made it yesterday, first class.

901
01:19:11,021 --> 01:19:13,809
Real fancy, now, chop-chop, upstairs,

902
01:19:13,857 --> 01:19:15,601
get dressed, make a story up to Bean.

903
01:19:16,777 --> 01:19:18,852
We got to get this road on the show.

904
01:21:02,905 --> 01:21:07,074
I just leaned against that.
I was yawning and I just..

905
01:21:07,783 --> 01:21:10,405
Turn it off!
I'm sorry...

906
01:24:07,012 --> 01:24:09,089
Hey... Julian!

907
01:24:18,981 --> 01:24:20,972
Julian!

908
01:24:23,483 --> 01:24:25,026
Julian!

909
01:24:32,742 --> 01:24:34,319
Julian?

910
01:24:38,496 --> 01:24:40,370
What the hell is going on?

911
01:24:41,082 --> 01:24:42,457
Julian?

912
01:24:46,295 --> 01:24:48,619
You drag me out to Arizona.

913
01:24:49,212 --> 01:24:51,584
To the god-damned horse-races?

914
01:24:52,466 --> 01:24:54,504
To do this job, right?

915
01:24:54,550 --> 01:24:57,124
To do this job, right.
To do this one last job...

916
01:24:58,179 --> 01:25:00,136
To kill somebody I don't even know-

917
01:25:00,181 --> 01:25:02,671
-so that you could live out
the rest of your life with greeks!

918
01:25:02,766 --> 01:25:04,924
Beautiful little greeks standing...

919
01:25:04,976 --> 01:25:08,344
We do... I do everything perfectly.
Not you... me! Perfectly.

920
01:25:08,520 --> 01:25:10,394
Did you see me, Julian?
I was brilliant!

921
01:25:11,022 --> 01:25:13,062
You got a clean shot,
I know you had a clean shot.

922
01:25:13,108 --> 01:25:15,064
And you don't take it!
What's going on?

923
01:25:15,610 --> 01:25:16,889
I've lost it, Danny.

924
01:25:16,944 --> 01:25:19,186
Really?
Then they're gonna kill you, Julian.

925
01:25:19,779 --> 01:25:21,357
But I've lost it...

926
01:25:21,739 --> 01:25:24,609
- That's an unacceptable answer!
- But it's the truth.

927
01:25:24,659 --> 01:25:26,283
Oh, please...

928
01:25:28,620 --> 01:25:31,075
Concentrate here, okey?
I need you to concentrate.

929
01:25:32,165 --> 01:25:34,999
Just look at me, Danny.
Look at me... I'm a wreck!

930
01:25:35,084 --> 01:25:37,291
- I'm a parody.
- Julian!

931
01:25:38,003 --> 01:25:40,375
- You got to get up there,
and finish this job. - No, no, no.

932
01:25:40,421 --> 01:25:43,505
No, just leave me alone, Danny.
Please, just forget everything.

933
01:25:44,592 --> 01:25:46,583
I can't believe,
I'm in a stairway-

934
01:25:46,634 --> 01:25:49,469
-  trying to convince you to
assassinate somebody!

935
01:25:50,096 --> 01:25:52,586
Just go... just go... go.

936
01:26:05,734 --> 01:26:07,062
No.

937
01:26:07,819 --> 01:26:12,194
- No, we're gonna do this.
- My God!

938
01:26:12,322 --> 01:26:15,157
Julian, you have to... you have to, okey?

939
01:26:15,242 --> 01:26:17,732
If you don't, they're gonna kill you,
do you understand me?

940
01:26:17,952 --> 01:26:19,231
- Do you understand?
- Yeah.

941
01:26:19,828 --> 01:26:22,402
And I won't let that happen.

942
01:26:22,831 --> 01:26:25,701
I refuse to let that happen,
how about that?

943
01:26:26,584 --> 01:26:29,455
We're gonna walk there together,
and I'll talk you through it.

944
01:26:29,504 --> 01:26:33,451
Okey? I'm gonna talk you right through it,
and you're gonna do the job.

945
01:26:34,090 --> 01:26:36,960
- Okey? - Yes.
- Okey, alright!

946
01:26:39,720 --> 01:26:41,877
Okey...

947
01:26:42,556 --> 01:26:44,299
Up, up, up!

948
01:26:44,933 --> 01:26:47,601
There you go.
Okey?

949
01:26:47,643 --> 01:26:50,311
- And you gonna stay up there with me.
- Yes, yes, yes.

950
01:26:54,314 --> 01:26:57,399
- Thank you.
- Alright, then...

951
01:26:57,443 --> 01:27:00,857
Let's go kill this fucker already,
and get the hell out of here!

952
01:27:22,254 --> 01:27:23,665
Thank you.

953
01:27:25,507 --> 01:27:27,380
Really, I mean it.

954
01:27:28,509 --> 01:27:30,300
I was a mess back there.

955
01:27:30,928 --> 01:27:34,971
You helped me.
You helped me alot.

956
01:27:38,725 --> 01:27:41,347
You know I think I can
handle the deviant-Julian.

957
01:27:42,062 --> 01:27:43,805
I can handle the lying-Julian.

958
01:27:43,855 --> 01:27:46,523
I can even handle the killing-Julian.

959
01:27:46,982 --> 01:27:50,398
I just don't know if I can handle
the weak-Julian.

960
01:27:52,488 --> 01:27:55,025
Well, enjoy it. It won't last...

961
01:27:55,614 --> 01:27:57,275
That's a given.

962
01:28:00,952 --> 01:28:04,451
Really...
it's no problem.

963
01:28:06,457 --> 01:28:10,583
You said it yourself..
I owed you.

964
01:28:12,712 --> 01:28:15,996
Do you think, if you hadn't open that door
late that night in Mexico city-

965
01:28:16,047 --> 01:28:18,502
- the two of us would be sitting
on this plane now?

966
01:28:22,219 --> 01:28:23,796
Probably not.

967
01:28:28,142 --> 01:28:30,713
Come on, Danny!
I just wanted to say I'm sorry.

968
01:28:30,768 --> 01:28:33,721
I know it's late,
and I'm a little fucked up, but...

969
01:28:33,978 --> 01:28:35,603
I'm sorry...

970
01:28:35,856 --> 01:28:38,097
Can't you see how guilty I feel?

971
01:28:39,400 --> 01:28:40,681
Danny!

972
01:28:41,485 --> 01:28:44,819
- Danny!
- Hold on, Julian! I'm coming.

973
01:28:49,617 --> 01:28:52,368
I don't know what'll I do
if I don't get this job.

974
01:28:54,955 --> 01:28:59,533
And you're sure if I kill off this guy,
you'll get the contract?

975
01:28:59,625 --> 01:29:01,416
It's the only competition.

976
01:29:01,709 --> 01:29:03,786
And you can live with that?

977
01:29:04,963 --> 01:29:07,749
- Yeah.
- You can live with that blood on you hands?

978
01:29:09,841 --> 01:29:14,586
That's what people do.
Dumb people...

979
01:29:15,680 --> 01:29:19,759
and successful people...
always live with blood on their hands?

980
01:29:24,437 --> 01:29:27,009
You became my friend that night, Julian.

981
01:29:27,982 --> 01:29:30,353
You became my life-long friend...

982
01:29:49,582 --> 01:29:51,788
I'm not going to do it for you.

983
01:29:52,709 --> 01:29:57,288
You're making it on a late night...
an exhausted desperate decision.

984
01:29:57,380 --> 01:30:00,831
And if I did it...
You would regret it instantly.

985
01:30:01,259 --> 01:30:05,172
And feel guilt and shame
for the rest of you life, believe me.

986
01:30:07,180 --> 01:30:09,137
I'm so scared, Julian.

987
01:30:10,724 --> 01:30:12,301
Guys like you...

988
01:30:13,351 --> 01:30:15,011
...you think you've no luck?

989
01:30:15,228 --> 01:30:17,304
But you got all the luck in the world.

990
01:30:18,981 --> 01:30:20,854
You just need to see it.

991
01:30:21,984 --> 01:30:24,106
She's at home,
waiting for you.

992
01:30:26,362 --> 01:30:28,105
If I did that job for you...

993
01:30:28,155 --> 01:30:31,606
...your luck would run bad,
for the rest of your days.

994
01:30:34,285 --> 01:30:36,656
You don't really wanna do it anyway,
I know you don't.

995
01:30:36,996 --> 01:30:38,869
You're not that type of person.

996
01:30:45,335 --> 01:30:47,458
That's why I like you.

997
01:30:48,880 --> 01:30:51,251
You're the exact opposite of me.

998
01:30:55,260 --> 01:30:57,501
You surprised me that night.

999
01:30:58,180 --> 01:31:00,218
I surprised myself.

1000
01:31:04,727 --> 01:31:06,967
I guess your boss must be satisfied, right?

1001
01:31:07,771 --> 01:31:11,933
You completed the assignment...
no longer on the hit-list.

1002
01:31:13,900 --> 01:31:18,063
Well, I'm no longer on the hit-list,
but I didn't do any assignment.

1003
01:31:19,947 --> 01:31:24,904
I don't understand, I thought your boss
wanted you to do this job!

1004
01:31:28,495 --> 01:31:34,663
My boss, mr Stick...
he was the job.

1005
01:31:37,253 --> 01:31:40,502
- Do you mean we just killed...
- We killed the man who wanted to kill me.

1006
01:31:42,049 --> 01:31:43,839
Problem solved.

1007
01:31:48,928 --> 01:31:50,672
You...

1008
01:31:52,474 --> 01:31:54,799
You son of a bitch!

1009
01:31:55,185 --> 01:31:57,011
Among many other things...

1010
01:31:57,687 --> 01:32:00,686
- Don't ever hit me again.
- Sorry...

1011
